org.spongepowered.api.event.block.tileentity

Interface TileEntityChangeEvent

  • All Superinterfaces:
    Cancellable, CauseTracked, Event, GameEvent, TileEntityEvent
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    SignChangeEvent

    public interface TileEntityChangeEvent
extends TileEntityEvent, CauseTracked, Cancellable
    Represents events where the DataManipulator of the TileEntity may change from the resolution of the event.

    An example of this would be SignChangeEvent where the data of the sign is set after the event.

    • Method Detail

      • getNewData

        DataManipulator<?,?> getNewData()
        Gets a copy of the new DataManipulator that will be offered to the TileEntity after event resolution.

        If desiring to change any data of this TileEntity, do so in this manipulator. Be sure to set this back with setNewData(DataManipulator).

        Returns:
        The data

      • setNewData

        void setNewData(DataManipulator<?,?> newData)
        Sets the DataManipulator that will be offered to the TileEntity after event resolution.
        Parameters:
        newData - The new manipulator to apply to the tile entity
        Throws:
        InvalidDataException - Depending on the event, this will be thrown if the manipulator being set isn't assignable from getNewData()
